recalls.Summary: Automobili Lamborghini (Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2012-2018 Lamborghini Aventador Coupe and Roadster vehicles.  The engine may stall unexpectedly during certain driving conditions such as when the accelerator pedal is released below 2000 rpms while the transmission is automatically down shifting to a lower gear.
recalls.Consequence: An engine stall can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Lamborghini will notify owners, and dealers will install updated engine software, free of charge.  The recall began August 3, 2018.  Owners may contact Lamborghini customer service at 1-866-681-6276.  Lamborghini's number for this recall is L73X-R.02.18.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels, particularly around the rear spoiler and side skirts, experience delamination where layers separate due to heat cycling and manufacturing defects. This affects the structural integrity and aerodynamics of the vehicle.
symptoms: Visible bubbling or warping of carbon fiber panels
White spots appearing under clear coat
issues.fix_description: Replace affected carbon fiber panels with updated parts that have improved resin bonding
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, park in shade when possible, regular inspection of carbon fiber components

issues.title: Electronic Stability Control Malfunction
issues.description: ESC system randomly disengages or provides false warnings due to faulty wheel speed sensors and control module software issues, potentially affecting vehicle stability during high-performance driving.
issues.fix_description: Replace wheel speed sensors and update ESC control module software
issues.prevention: Regular diagnostic scans during maintenance, avoid aggressive driving when warning lights are present

issues.title: Transmission Overheating in Track Mode
issues.description: The ISR (Independent Shifting Rod) transmission overheats during extended track sessions, causing the system to enter limp mode and reducing performance. Inadequate cooling for high-performance use.
issues.fix_description: Install additional transmission cooler and update cooling system software
issues.prevention: Allow proper cool-down periods between track sessions, monitor transmission temperature

issues.title: Rear Wing Actuator Failure
issues.description: The active aerodynamics rear wing actuator motor fails, preventing the wing from adjusting position automatically based on driving modes and speed, compromising aerodynamic performance.
symptoms: Rear wing stuck in one position
Grinding noise from rear spoiler area
issues.fix_description: Replace rear wing actuator motor and recalibrate aerodynamics system
issues.prevention: Regular system checks, avoid forcing wing movement manually

issues.title: Engine Bay Fire Risk
issues.description: Fuel line connections near the engine bay can develop leaks due to heat stress, creating potential fire hazard. Heat shields may also become loose, increasing fire risk.
symptoms: Visible fuel stains in engine bay
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel lines with improved heat-resistant versions and secure all heat shields
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of engine bay, immediate attention to fuel odors

issues.title: Infotainment System Boot Loop
issues.description: The central infotainment display gets stuck in continuous restart cycles, preventing access to climate control, navigation, and vehicle settings. System becomes unresponsive to inputs.
issues.fix_description: Replace infotainment control unit and update software to latest version
issues.prevention: Avoid interrupting system updates, regular software maintenance

issues.title: Brake Disc Warping and Cracking
issues.description: Carbon ceramic brake discs develop hairline cracks and warping under high-temperature conditions during track use, leading to reduced braking performance and potential safety concerns.
issues.fix_description: Replace carbon ceramic brake discs with updated versions designed for higher heat tolerance
issues.prevention: Proper brake cooling periods, gradual brake warming before aggressive use

issues.title: Suspension Sensor Calibration Issues
issues.description: Adaptive suspension height sensors lose calibration, causing the vehicle to ride incorrectly and triggering constant error messages. The system may not adjust properly for different driving modes.
issues.fix_description: Recalibrate suspension sensors and replace any faulty height sensors
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme suspension adjustments, regular system diagnostics

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Electronic door handle mechanisms fail to operate properly, particularly in cold weather. Handles may not extend or retract correctly, potentially trapping occupants.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle actuator motors and lubricate mechanisms
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication of door mechanisms, especially before cold weather

issues.title: Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: The naturally aspirated V12 engine experiences higher than normal oil consumption, particularly during high-RPM operation, requiring frequent oil level monitoring and top-offs.
issues.fix_description: Check valve stem seals and piston rings, use recommended oil grade
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use only specified oil grade, avoid prolonged high-RPM operation

editorial.tagline: The ultimate naturally-aspirated V12 swan song
editorial.hero_blurb: The Aventador SVJ represents Lamborghini's final and most extreme naturally-aspirated V12 flagship. With its track-focused aerodynamics and thunderous 759-hp engine, it's a visceral farewell to the analog supercar era.
editorial.essence: The SVJ is Lamborghini's uncompromising pursuit of track perfection wrapped in road-legal bodywork. It combines old-school naturally-aspirated fury with cutting-edge aerodynamics to create the most extreme Aventador ever built.
editorial.heritage: The final evolution of Lamborghini's flagship V12 lineage that began with the original Countach. Built on the Aventador platform that debuted in 2011, the SVJ serves as the ultimate expression of Sant'Agata's naturally-aspirated philosophy before the hybrid era.
editorial.design_philosophy: Aerodynamics and aggression define every surface, with active aero elements and extreme bodywork designed to slice through air and dominate racetracks while maintaining Lamborghini's signature angular aesthetic.
editorial.motorsport_history: Holds the Nürburgring production car lap record (6:44.97) and incorporates lessons learned from Lamborghini's Super Trofeo racing series and Squadra Corse motorsport division.
editorial.engine_character: The 6.5L V12 delivers intoxicating linear power with a ferocious top-end rush. Every throttle input unleashes a symphony of mechanical fury that builds relentlessly to an 8,500-rpm crescendo.
editorial.transmission_feel: The single-clutch automated manual fires off shifts with violent precision, delivering jarring but addictive gear changes that remind you this is a racing machine disguised as a road car.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Brutally stiff and uncompromising, with active suspension and rear-wheel steering creating supernatural precision on track while punishing imperfect surfaces with bone-jarring feedback.
editorial.steering_feel: Heavy, direct, and communicative with zero isolation from the road. Every surface imperfection telegraphs through the wheel, creating an intimate connection between driver and asphalt.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive carbon-ceramic discs provide immense stopping power with a firm, progressive pedal that inspires complete confidence even under extreme track conditions.
editorial.sound_signature: An apocalyptic V12 wail that transitions from menacing idle rumble to spine-tingling shriek, with pops and crackles on overrun that echo like gunfire through tunnels.
editorial.ideal_owner: Track-focused enthusiasts who prioritize pure driving experience over comfort, collectors seeking the last great naturally-aspirated V12, and drivers who want maximum drama from their supercars.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters, comfort seekers, those wanting refined grand touring capabilities, or anyone intimidated by aggressive, uncompromising performance machines.
editorial.buyers_summary: Buy the cleanest, lowest-mileage example you can afford as these represent the end of an era. Expect astronomical running costs but unmatched naturally-aspirated V12 thrills.

images.prompt_used:
SUBJECT: Lamborghini Aventador SVJ (2018-2021), pristine showroom condition.

SETTING: Private collector's industrial warehouse garage. Brick warehouse with arched windows OR modern concrete gallery OR vintage factory with timber beams.

COMPOSITION: Front 3/4 hero angle showing front fascia and driver's side profile. Show COMPLETE car (all four wheels, both bumpers, full roofline). Camera at knee height.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
